✅ 1. Prerequisites
Make sure you have:

An Azure subscription (Free or Paid).

Azure CLI installed (az version) — or use the Azure Cloud Shell.

kubectl installed for managing the cluster.

(Optional) Terraform or Bicep for IaC.

1.az login
2.az group create --name aks-rg --location eastus
3.az aks create   --resource-group aks-rg1   --name myAKSCluster   --node-count 1   --node-vm-size Standard_B2s   --enable-addons monitoring   --generate-ssh-keys
4.curl -LO https://dl.k8s.io/release/v1.31.0/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl
sudo chmod +x ./kubectl
sudo mv kubectl /usr/local/bin
kubectl version 
5.az provider register --namespace Microsoft.ContainerService
az provider register --namespace Microsoft.Monitor


6. az aks get-credentials --resource-group aks-rg --name myAKSCluster

venu [ ~ ]$ kubectl get nodes
NAME                                STATUS   ROLES    AGE    VERSION
aks-nodepool1-58118951-vmss000000   Ready    <none>   9m4s   v1.32.6
venu [ ~ ]$ kubectl create deployment nginx --image=nginx
kubectl expose deployment nginx --port=80 --type=LoadBalancer
deployment.apps/nginx created
service/nginx exposed
